	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Office of the Jewish Messenger</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>119 West Houston Street</placeName>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>May 10th 1864</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Esteemed Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">The Bible &#38; prayer<lb/> books reached us yesterday<lb/> in good order.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">As regards the<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> you inquired about&#44; the<lb/> prices are &#36;12 and &#36;25.&#8212; to<lb/> you&#44; &#36;10 and &#36;22.  Are these<lb/> rates conformable to your expecta<lb/>tions&#63;  If so&#44; let us know<lb/> &#38; the number you order will<lb/> be promptly forwarded.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We sympathize in<lb/> your recital concerning advanced<lb/> rates of labor.  There appears to<lb/> be no help for it.  We can only submit.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My father desires me to<lb/> say that he knows nothing<lb/> whatever of the matter you<lb/> refer to&#44; concerning the inquiry<lb/> put to him by <persName>Mr Solis</persName>.  He<lb/> is entirely ignorant of the affair<lb/> and has not been applied to by<lb/> anybody with reference to it.  He<lb/> says that he &#8220;thought you knew<lb/> him better than to put such<lb/> a question.&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With respect to the Board of<lb/> Delegates&#44; I can inform you<lb/> of one accession&#8212;that of the<lb/> <placeName>Clinton St.</placeName> congregation of this city.<lb/>  I am trying to bring the others<lb/> in&#44; but the <persName>Wise</persName>&#45;Germanic influence<lb/> is too strong.  If you have drafted<lb/> any document you would like to<lb/> have issued&#44; you might send it<lb/> to me as soon as you please<lb/> There will be a meeting of the</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>Executive Committee in a week or two.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The Free School movement has<lb/> progressed quite favorably.  Some<lb/> 400 members at &#36;5 a year have been<lb/> reported by the Presidents of five congrega<lb/>tions &#38; two of these will increase their<lb/> lists to 200 each&#44; while an aggregate<lb/> of 1000 is confidently looked for<lb/> in a very few weeks.  Donations&#44; also&#44;<lb/> are coming in rapidly.  I think<lb/> they will have at least 2 schools<lb/> open in <date>September</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Trusting you are quite well&#44;<lb/> and expecting to see you before<lb/> many weeks at <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> if not here I am Rev &#38; dear sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M. J. Isaacs</persName>.</p>
				<p>My parents &#38; <persName>Jacob</persName> wish to<lb/> be remembered.</p>
				<p>Please to send me <hi rend="underline">at once</hi> to<lb/> <placeName>150 Nassau Street</placeName>&#44; <hi rend="underline">and not to</hi></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><hi rend="underline"><placeName>Houston St.</placeName></hi> as I don&#39;t wish<lb/> father to know anything about<lb/> it&#44; a copy of your Bible<lb/> <hi rend="underline">unbound</hi> &#38; on the best paper.<lb/>  I intend it as a present to<lb/> my parents for their <hi rend="underline">silver</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">wedding</hi>&#44; and wish to have it<lb/> bound under my own eye in<lb/> a style that may not be<lb/> always ready at your binder&#39;s.<lb/> &#40;with all due respect to <persName>Che<add>&#63;</add></persName>&#41;<lb/> Please send it without fail<lb/> to <persName>M. S. Isaacs</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>150 Nassau St.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><placeName>N.Y.</placeName></p>
				<p>by Express</p>
		</body>
